</i> ‘power’, but soon assumed a variety of forms such as <i>Amauri</i> and <i>Emauri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":29,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":38,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Emery De Sacy was born before 1186, in Saussay, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France as the son of Rogo De Sacy. He married Agnes about 1227. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died before 25 July 1253, in Pamber, Hampshire, England."},"et":{"Bef 1186–before 25 July 1253":"enne 1186–enne 25. juulit 1253","1186–1253":"1186–1253","–1253":"–1253","1228–1292":"1228–1292","1233–Male":"1233–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1170–1206":"1170–1206","before 25 July 1253":"enne 25. juulit 1253","1253":"1253","1186":"1186","1292":"1292","1170":"1170","Bef 1186":"enne 1186","1206":"1206","1228":"1228","1215":"1215","about 1206":"umbes 1206","1224":"1224","1233":"1233","about 1227":"umbes 1227","about 1233":"umbes 1233"," 1228":"1228","England":"England","Saussay, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France":"Saussay, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Pamber, Hampshire, England":"Pamber, Hampshire, England"},"fi":{"Bef 1186–before 25 July 1253":"ennen vuotta 1186–ennen vuotta 25. heinäkuuta 1253","1186–1253":"1186–1253","–1